-- Hashimoto and Bhutani Leave Canadian Imperial for National Bank
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-08-30T19:18:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-30/hashimoto-and-bhutani-leave-canadian-imperial-for-national-bank.html
National Bank of Canada (NA)  said it
hired fixed-income bankers Steven Hashimoto and Sunil Bhutani
from Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce.  National Bank added Hashimoto as director of government
syndication and Bhutani as managing director and head of
government finance and syndication, Claude Breton, a bank
spokesman in  Montreal , said in an e-mail.  Hashimoto was previously executive director of debt capital
markets at CIBC, and Bhutani was managing director of the unit
at the Toronto-based bank. They will be joining National Bank in
Toronto on Nov. 1. CIBC is Canadaâ€™s fifth-biggest bank, while
National is the sixth largest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
